1
00:00:39,900 --> 00:00:41,367
<i>Okay, Felma, be honest with me.</i>

2
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:43,700
<i>What if you see him right now?
What are you going to do?</i>

3
00:00:43,833 --> 00:00:45,833
<i>I no longer feel
anything for him.</i>

4
00:00:45,967 --> 00:00:48,033
<i>You're changing the topic!
Whatever!</i>

5
00:00:48,167 --> 00:00:49,833
<i> Manuel! What's wrong with you?</i>

6
00:00:49,967 --> 00:00:51,200
<i> I've been calling your name.</i>

7
00:00:51,333 --> 00:00:53,267
<i>You went to Daisy's place, Jeff.</i>

8
00:00:53,400 --> 00:00:54,567
<i> Why didn't you talk to her?</i>

9
00:00:54,700 --> 00:00:56,000
<i>I don't know
how to approach them.</i>

10
00:00:56,133 --> 00:00:58,600
<i>Just admit that you're a coward
like your father.</i>

11
00:00:58,733 --> 00:01:00,300
<i> Don't compare me to your dad.</i>

12
00:01:00,433 --> 00:01:02,500
<i>I went abroad,
and I did everything I could.</i>

13
00:01:02,633 --> 00:01:04,000
<i> What did you do in return?</i>

14
00:01:04,133 --> 00:01:06,167
<i>You spent all
my hard-earned money.</i>

15
00:01:06,300 --> 00:01:08,533
<i>Hazel, why don't you listen to
what they have to say?</i>

16
00:01:08,700 --> 00:01:09,700
<i> They're your family.</i>

17
00:01:09,833 --> 00:01:12,133
<i>You have to forgive each other.</i>

18
00:01:13,167 --> 00:01:14,667
<i> You want to talk to Felma?</i>

19
00:01:14,800 --> 00:01:15,900
<i> So that's the reason,</i>

20
00:01:16,033 --> 00:01:17,833
<i>why you want me to get along
with my siblings.</i>

21
00:01:17,967 --> 00:01:20,567
<i>You want to reconnect
with Felma.</i>

22
00:01:20,700 --> 00:01:21,967
<i>- Hey!
- I came here,</i>

23
00:01:22,100 --> 00:01:23,633
<i>-to stop you.
-Bro, If you don't want to help,</i>

24
00:01:23,767 --> 00:01:25,333
<i>then don't! But don't try
to stop me!</i>

25
00:01:25,467 --> 00:01:26,933
<i>- You can't!
- Manuel?</i>

26
00:01:42,267 --> 00:01:43,100
Ma'am.

27
00:01:49,067 --> 00:01:50,533
Hey, Felma.

28
00:01:50,667 --> 00:01:52,500
Why do you look like that?

29
00:01:53,867 --> 00:01:55,333
I thought...

30
00:01:57,133 --> 00:01:59,200
I saw Manuel outside.

31
00:02:00,133 --> 00:02:01,900
What? You saw Manuel?

32
00:02:03,867 --> 00:02:05,933
What is he doing here?

33
00:02:06,700 --> 00:02:07,933
Why is he doing here?

34
00:02:08,067 --> 00:02:10,733
Were you able to talk?
What did you say?

35
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:15,033
We didn't get to talk.

36
00:02:16,433 --> 00:02:18,900
Wait a minute, Felma...

37
00:02:19,033 --> 00:02:22,300
Manuel, the cheater
is in Canada.

38
00:02:23,100 --> 00:02:25,200
Maybe you're just seeing things.

39
00:02:25,333 --> 00:02:27,767
And if he's here in
the Philippines,

40
00:02:27,900 --> 00:02:30,100
Abel would have told me already.

41
00:02:30,233 --> 00:02:33,033
That's what I'm saying,
I thought I saw him with Abel.

42
00:02:35,100 --> 00:02:35,967
I thought...

43
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:39,733
I really thought I saw him.

44
00:02:39,867 --> 00:02:41,667
I suddenly felt nervous.

45
00:02:43,133 --> 00:02:46,833
Felma, what's going on with you?

46
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:49,833
Don't tell me you're still
thinking about him.

47
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:52,800
I'm not!

48
00:02:56,167 --> 00:02:57,133
His name just came up,

49
00:02:57,267 --> 00:03:00,467
because of Jeffrey's issue
with Daisy.

50
00:03:01,300 --> 00:03:05,700
Andrea told him that
he's just like Manuel.

51
00:03:06,500 --> 00:03:08,267
That he abandoned his family.

52
00:03:09,100 --> 00:03:12,067
And then, because of my upcoming
interview with Filipino moms,

53
00:03:12,367 --> 00:03:15,900
old photos of Manuel were dug up
from our photo album.

54
00:03:16,133 --> 00:03:17,500
Coleen kept all of them.

55
00:03:18,667 --> 00:03:23,067
The pain suddenly came back,
along with the anger.

56
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:25,133
Felma, calm down.

57
00:03:25,267 --> 00:03:27,633
Don't let Manuel affect you
like this.

58
00:03:28,700 --> 00:03:29,967
That's the thing.

59
00:03:30,967 --> 00:03:33,333
Noah told me the same thing.

60
00:03:34,300 --> 00:03:36,333
Then that's what you should do.

61
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:51,267
Where have you been?

62
00:03:52,700 --> 00:03:54,367
You went to see Felma,
didn't you?

63
00:03:58,733 --> 00:03:59,700
I did.

64
00:04:00,533 --> 00:04:04,567
I wanted to apologize to her and
our children in person.

65
00:04:06,167 --> 00:04:07,433
How dare you!

66
00:04:08,700 --> 00:04:10,767
You're so shameless.

67
00:04:11,533 --> 00:04:14,467
Didn't I tell you not
to see her?

68
00:04:14,967 --> 00:04:15,900
Hazel...

69
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:19,033
I've been away from them for
eighteen years!

70
00:04:19,867 --> 00:04:21,667
Can't I see them,
even just for a moment?

71
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:25,167
What's the point of seeing her
for a minute?

72
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:28,200
You'll get back together
with her?

73
00:04:28,367 --> 00:04:29,400
To be forgiven!

74
00:04:29,533 --> 00:04:31,167
I don't believe you!

75
00:04:32,200 --> 00:04:33,700
What is it, Manuel?

76
00:04:34,067 --> 00:04:35,500
What did you talk about?

77
00:04:36,233 --> 00:04:38,733
Maybe she can't wait
to get back together with you.

78
00:04:38,867 --> 00:04:40,100
Hazel, can you stop this?

79
00:04:40,233 --> 00:04:42,967
No way! I'm your wife!

80
00:04:43,400 --> 00:04:44,733
I have the right!

81
00:04:44,867 --> 00:04:46,867
I will never let her
take you from me!

82
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:48,767
Hazel, she's not going
to take me from you!

83
00:04:48,900 --> 00:04:51,067
I didn't even get to see her!

84
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:52,700
Tell me!

85
00:04:52,833 --> 00:04:54,867
What did she tell you?
What is your plan!

86
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:55,867
- Tell me!
- Stop!

87
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:57,400
Tell me now, Manuel!

88
00:04:57,533 --> 00:04:58,933
Tell me! What's your plan?

89
00:04:59,067 --> 00:05:00,267
- Hazel!
- Because I know,

90
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:01,933
- Mom...
- I'll find out eventually.

91
00:05:02,100 --> 00:05:03,800
Mom! Dad!

92
00:05:04,867 --> 00:05:06,667
Your mom is getting
paranoid again.

93
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:07,867
She's having
all kinds of thoughts!

94
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:09,533
Where are you going now?

95
00:05:09,667 --> 00:05:10,900
- We're not done talking yet!
- Mom!

96
00:05:11,033 --> 00:05:11,900
- Manuel!
- Mom, stop!

97
00:05:28,100 --> 00:05:29,100
Hello, Jessica?

98
00:05:29,500 --> 00:05:30,967
Dad, where are you?

99
00:05:31,967 --> 00:05:34,300
I'm outside, I'm just trying to
cool my head.

100
00:05:35,400 --> 00:05:37,033
Dad, what happened?

101
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:39,200
<i> It's your mom.</i>

102
00:05:39,933 --> 00:05:41,400
She's been accusing me of all
sorts of things.

103
00:05:41,533 --> 00:05:43,133
She even called me a liar.

104
00:05:43,267 --> 00:05:44,967
<i> Dad, just let it go.</i>

105
00:05:45,300 --> 00:05:48,867
We both know that mom can be
a bit difficult sometimes.

106
00:05:49,167 --> 00:05:51,100
Just talk it out with her.

107
00:05:52,733 --> 00:05:54,633
What do you want me to do?

108
00:05:54,767 --> 00:05:56,267
Dad, please.

109
00:05:56,800 --> 00:05:58,267
<i> Okay fine.</i>

110
00:05:58,800 --> 00:06:01,633
I'll talk to her
when I get home.

111
00:06:02,733 --> 00:06:04,567
Thanks, Dad. I love you.

112
00:06:05,300 --> 00:06:06,167
I love you, Dear.

113
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:08,333
Bye, Dad.

114
00:06:09,767 --> 00:06:11,867
Hey, did you talk to your dad?

115
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:13,667
Yes, he's just letting off
steam.

116
00:06:13,800 --> 00:06:15,100
He'll be right back, Mom.

117
00:06:15,233 --> 00:06:16,300
Where is he?

118
00:06:19,400 --> 00:06:21,600
You talked to him,
and you didn't ask where he is?

119
00:06:22,100 --> 00:06:24,133
How are we going to find out
where your dad is?

120
00:06:40,133 --> 00:06:41,567
<i> Yes!</i>

121
00:06:41,733 --> 00:06:43,633
<i> We're having a baby!</i>

122
00:06:43,767 --> 00:06:46,167
<i> Be quiet! It's embarrassing!</i>

123
00:06:47,800 --> 00:06:50,167
<i>This is the right time
to get married.</i>

124
00:06:52,333 --> 00:06:55,433
<i>Playing hide and
seek in the moonlight!</i>

125
00:06:55,567 --> 00:06:57,000
<i> When I count to ten...</i>

126
00:06:57,133 --> 00:06:58,500
<i>- you'd better be hiding!
- Aren't you supposed to count?</i>

127
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:01,300
<i>- Okay!
- Go on, no cheating.</i>

128
00:07:01,433 --> 00:07:03,733
<i>- You better be hiding!
- Go hide!</i>

129
00:07:03,867 --> 00:07:05,233
I miss you all so much.

130
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:32,367
<i> Is Dad the reason,</i>

131
00:07:32,500 --> 00:07:36,200
<i>we don't go to Luntian Park
anymore?</i>

132
00:07:37,267 --> 00:07:40,533
<i>That place is
very special to us...</i>

133
00:07:41,633 --> 00:07:42,900
<i> But when...</i>

134
00:07:43,033 --> 00:07:44,100
<i> he cheated on me...</i>

135
00:07:44,433 --> 00:07:46,000
<i> and abandoned us...</i>

136
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:48,900
<i>I can't bear to see
that place again.</i>

137
00:07:50,533 --> 00:07:51,900
<i> You can do it, Felma.</i>

138
00:07:52,667 --> 00:07:54,633
<i>You can go inside
that park once again.</i>

139
00:08:37,100 --> 00:08:38,433
<i> I can do it.</i>

140
00:08:39,500 --> 00:08:40,867
<i> I did it.</i>

141
00:08:46,767 --> 00:08:50,800
<i>From now on, I won't let you
affect me again, Manuel.</i>

142
00:08:54,033 --> 00:08:55,533
<i> Never again.</i>

143
00:09:36,700 --> 00:09:37,933
Love?

144
00:09:53,867 --> 00:09:55,133
Felma, how are you?

145
00:09:57,267 --> 00:09:58,800
Felma, wait, can we talk?

146
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:01,000
I don't want to talk to you!

147
00:10:01,867 --> 00:10:02,900
We have nothing left to talk
about!

148
00:10:03,033 --> 00:10:04,267
Yes, we do, we have plenty of
things to talk about.

149
00:10:04,567 --> 00:10:06,067
I have a lot to tell you.

150
00:10:07,833 --> 00:10:09,233
Whatever it is...

151
00:10:09,567 --> 00:10:11,300
I don't want to hear it!

152
00:10:12,900 --> 00:10:14,967
Can I see the kids, please?

153
00:10:15,100 --> 00:10:17,400
I want to see them, Felma.
Please.

154
00:10:18,167 --> 00:10:20,000
I don't want you to see my kids.

155
00:10:20,800 --> 00:10:22,500
Their life is peaceful now.

156
00:10:25,667 --> 00:10:27,367
Felma, I know that you hate me.

157
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:30,467
But you can't decide for
the kids.

158
00:10:31,267 --> 00:10:33,967
I'm their father! I have the
right to see them!

159
00:10:34,633 --> 00:10:35,900
What did you say?

160
00:10:36,700 --> 00:10:39,433
You abandoned them for almost
eighteen years.

161
00:10:40,267 --> 00:10:42,333
And now you want to see them?

162
00:10:43,200 --> 00:10:44,633
Because you're their father?

163
00:10:45,767 --> 00:10:47,067
<i> He lied to us!</i>

164
00:10:47,200 --> 00:10:48,933
<i> Mom, is it true?</i>

165
00:10:49,067 --> 00:10:51,233
<i>- Of what?
- Dad has a new baby?</i>

166
00:10:51,367 --> 00:10:52,533
<i> He has a new family?</i>

167
00:10:52,667 --> 00:10:56,400
<i>It's true, your dad has
a new family now.</i>

168
00:10:56,667 --> 00:10:59,133
<i>What? My daughter is not
a cheater.</i>

169
00:10:59,267 --> 00:11:02,433
<i>I wasn't able to study for the
exam, Mom.</i>

170
00:11:02,567 --> 00:11:05,067
<i>Because I was taking care of
Coleen.</i>

171
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:07,000
<i> Why didn't you tell me?</i>

172
00:11:07,133 --> 00:11:08,433
<i>How are you going
to take care of her,</i>

173
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:11,300
<i>when you're always tired and
drunk?</i>

174
00:11:11,433 --> 00:11:13,200
<i>So you're the mother of this
thief!</i>

175
00:11:13,333 --> 00:11:14,633
<i> My son is not a thief!</i>

176
00:11:14,900 --> 00:11:16,333
<i> He stole my wallet!</i>

177
00:11:16,467 --> 00:11:20,300
<i>I did it so you can pay
the car owner for the damage.</i>

178
00:11:20,700 --> 00:11:22,133
<i>I don't want you to go to jail!</i>

179
00:11:22,267 --> 00:11:23,967
<i> I don't want that to happen!</i>

180
00:11:25,133 --> 00:11:29,833
You have no idea what
my children went through...

181
00:11:30,833 --> 00:11:32,167
when you abandoned us.

182
00:11:33,167 --> 00:11:35,733
What rights are you
talking about?

183
00:11:49,667 --> 00:11:50,700
Tracking app, right?

184
00:11:50,833 --> 00:11:52,300
Our phone has a tracking app.

185
00:11:52,733 --> 00:11:53,733
What?

186
00:11:53,867 --> 00:11:55,633
Don't tell me you're going
to track him?

187
00:11:55,767 --> 00:11:58,967
Mom, you can only use that
when it's emergency.

188
00:12:00,567 --> 00:12:01,667
Oh, well.

189
00:12:01,967 --> 00:12:03,133
This is an emergency.

190
00:12:04,267 --> 00:12:07,000
Now, show me how to use that
tracking app or else!

191
00:12:07,133 --> 00:12:08,333
You'll get in big trouble
with me.

192
00:12:16,067 --> 00:12:17,667
Felma, I'm sorry about
what I said.

193
00:12:20,100 --> 00:12:22,100
I didn't mean to say it
in a bad way.

194
00:12:25,633 --> 00:12:28,000
I just want to see our children.

195
00:12:32,667 --> 00:12:34,367
I really miss them.

196
00:12:35,667 --> 00:12:37,733
Don't worry about them.

197
00:12:39,167 --> 00:12:40,267
They're doing well.

198
00:12:42,400 --> 00:12:44,733
Because I raised them well.

199
00:12:45,133 --> 00:12:46,667
I know, Felma.
I know.

200
00:12:46,800 --> 00:12:48,600
You took good care of them.

201
00:12:49,267 --> 00:12:50,933
I want to see all of you.

202
00:12:51,067 --> 00:12:53,367
The four of you.

203
00:12:54,500 --> 00:12:57,600
I want to personally
ask all of you for forgiveness.

204
00:12:57,733 --> 00:13:00,933
For everything that I've done.

205
00:13:02,467 --> 00:13:04,033
It's too late now.

206
00:13:04,167 --> 00:13:05,300
Felma.

207
00:13:05,633 --> 00:13:06,733
I know.

208
00:13:07,633 --> 00:13:09,900
But this is the only chance
I will get to see them.

209
00:13:10,033 --> 00:13:11,200
I might not have another chance.

210
00:13:11,333 --> 00:13:13,500
We're going back
to Canada tonight.

211
00:13:13,833 --> 00:13:15,100
Please, I'm begging you.

212
00:13:16,467 --> 00:13:19,867
I just want to see Andrea,
Jeffrey, and Coleen.

213
00:13:20,767 --> 00:13:22,467
Please, Felma.

214
00:13:23,100 --> 00:13:24,767
I'm begging you.

215
00:13:33,433 --> 00:13:35,567
This is Jeff, and Andrea.

216
00:13:35,700 --> 00:13:36,600
They're Felma's kids.

217
00:13:36,733 --> 00:13:37,600
- Abby.
- Hello.

218
00:13:37,733 --> 00:13:39,800
- Hi, nice to meet you.
- Hello, Miss Abby.

219
00:13:41,100 --> 00:13:42,267
- And the pictures?
- Oh, yes.

220
00:13:42,400 --> 00:13:44,833
These are the photos
my mom picked.

221
00:13:48,433 --> 00:13:50,533
You don't have any of
your father's pictures?

222
00:13:51,567 --> 00:13:55,367
We threw away
the pictures of him.

223
00:13:55,533 --> 00:13:57,900
It would have been nice
to show his picture,

224
00:13:58,033 --> 00:13:58,967
even just once.

225
00:13:59,100 --> 00:14:00,000
You really don't have any
of his pictures?

226
00:14:00,133 --> 00:14:02,333
Sorry, he's no longer part of
our family.

227
00:14:02,467 --> 00:14:04,467
- Miss Abby! Here!
- We're not going to include...

228
00:14:05,033 --> 00:14:06,767
I have my dad's pictures
in there.

229
00:14:08,467 --> 00:14:10,267
Oh, so you saved some of
his pictures.

230
00:14:10,400 --> 00:14:11,700
Excuse me,

231
00:14:11,833 --> 00:14:15,733
I'll just have these collated by
the producer for sequencing.

232
00:14:15,867 --> 00:14:17,300
Oh, Miss Abby, can you...

233
00:14:17,433 --> 00:14:19,367
can you not include
those pictures? Please.

234
00:14:19,500 --> 00:14:22,033
I promise, we'll only use one.

235
00:14:22,533 --> 00:14:24,233
Mark, you can set up now.

236
00:14:24,567 --> 00:14:25,633
Errol, come with me.

237
00:14:30,667 --> 00:14:31,667
Let me go!

238
00:14:31,800 --> 00:14:34,167
You chose Hazel and
your daughter with her over us.

239
00:14:34,300 --> 00:14:35,300
You can go to them!

240
00:14:35,433 --> 00:14:36,633
Felma, I'm begging you!

241
00:14:36,767 --> 00:14:38,467
I just want to see our children!

242
00:14:42,100 --> 00:14:43,300
Go back to Canada!

243
00:14:43,433 --> 00:14:45,867
You don't have
a family here anymore!

244
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:47,300
Felma, I'm not going back
to Canada...

245
00:14:47,433 --> 00:14:48,433
without seeing them!

246
00:14:48,567 --> 00:14:49,633
You won't let go of me?

247
00:14:49,767 --> 00:14:51,000
I will scream!

248
00:14:52,833 --> 00:14:54,767
I knew it!

249
00:14:58,067 --> 00:14:59,467
You're both shameless!

250
00:15:01,667 --> 00:15:04,300
You really went
to see your mistress, Manuel.

251
00:15:04,433 --> 00:15:06,300
And you, Felma,

252
